Workaround is to spin the event loop for 100ms after setBusy(false) and before closing editor.

    Display display = form.getDisplay();
    long t = System.currentTimeMillis() + 100;
    while (!form.isDisposed() && System.currentTimeMillis() < t) {
        if (!display.readAndDispatch()) {
            display.sleep();
        }
    }
